Italy’s Inflation Rate Rises to 30-Month High on Energy Prices

-- B y   L o r e n z o   T o t a r o
-- 
2011-05-31T09:00:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-31/italy-s-inflation-rate-rises-to-30-month-high-on-energy-prices.html
The inflation rate in  Italy ,  Europe ’s
fourth-biggest economy rose in May to the highest in more than
two years, boosted by rising food and energy prices.  Inflation based on European Union measurements rose to 3
percent, the highest since October 2008, from 2.9 percent in
April, Rome-based national statistics office Istat said in a
preliminary report today. The April rate was higher than the 2.9
percent median forecast of 17 economists surveyed by Bloomberg
News. Prices advanced 0.2 percent from the previous month.  Based on Italian methodology, prices gained 0.1 percent
from April and rose 2.6 percent from a year earlier.  The inflation rate in the 17-nation euro region fell to
held at 2.7 percent in May from 2.8 percent the previous month,
the EU’s  statistics office  said in a preliminary report today.
percent.  Istat will release final consumer-price data on June 16.  To contact the reporter on this story:
